issues.body:
Hi, thank you for this plugin. Is there any way to enable equation numbering? When using MathJaX, I can add the following to the HTML header to enable equation numbering:
```
<script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
MathJax.Hub.Config({
  TeX: { equationNumbers: { autoNumber: "AMS" } }
});
</script>
```
Is there any way to do this in Wordpress?

issue_comments.body:
Yes thank you by replacing a couple of lines of code in the mathjax php file.

```
public static function filter_br_tags_on_math( $content ) {
    return preg_replace_callback(
        '/(<math.*>.*<\/math>)/isU',
        function ( $matches ) {
            return str_replace( array( '<br/>', '<br />', '<br>' ) , '' , $matches[0] );
        },
        $content
    );
}
```

Currently I'm only using `mhchem` to add chemical formulas in MathJax.
I'm adding it with the following snippet, placed in the body of the pages, where MathJax is loaded:

```
<script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
  MathJax.Hub.Config({
    TeX: {
      extensions: ["mhchem.js"]
    }
  });
</script>
```

See this page in the documentation for other extensions: http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/tex.html#tex-and-latex-extensions

I think that you should add support for all of them as they are already included in the MathJax package but not loaded by default. So if somebody needed to use them, they could simply check a box in the WordPress backend and the extension would be added to their site.
